Posted honest feedback to their website reviewing a tungsten guide rod for a 43X. I gave their product 1 star (bought quite a bit from them in the past with no issues until now) since it took the weapon from perfect to unreliable ( average 3 of 10 rounds misfired with no other changes).  Low and behold, my review never made it to their website.  Looking through, it appears anything below 3 stars is filtered out for the sake of good-to-great product reviews and ultimately higher sales. Bottom line, if they are willing to bury bad product reviews for the sake of selling parts, I'll take my business elsewhere.

The back story: I bought a new "standard" tungsten guide rod took my Glock from super reliable to unreliable (3 of 10 rounds misfireed).  Swapped back to OEM...perfect again.  My issue is their lack of honesty and transparency on the website.  If a product is a problem, they appear to be willing to hide it for the sake of sales.

They won't get my business again due to these trust issues.< /review>

Here's my experience after being in the store 3 times.

1st time I visited this business I was promptly greeted and helped by a very nice lady. She found the parts I was after right away and gave me some options on their selection. I was happy with the purchase (barrel, and trigger kit), and they fit perfectly.

2nd visit purchased upper slide kit, greeted just the same as before but by a different sales person and had what I was looking for in less than 5 minutes thanks to the staff and out the door. 3rd visit, staff greeted me promptly again and helped me with a small issue on the slide and offered to help me with one more piece to complete it before I left the store. Everything fits and functions just like it should.

Very friendly in store staff. Prices are more than other places online, but I like quality aftermaket parts as well as OEM Glock parts. After market parts seem to be quality made and function without error so far. Every part I've purchased from this store has had no problem with fitment and performs as expected or better. I have no online ordering experience as I live near the store. Being able to have these parts readily available is why I like this store. Freakin' Awesome!

I'll admit I'm a newbie when it comes to Glocks. I grew up as a hunting enthusiast mostly with long rifles and shotguns. The only pistol I'd fired before was a .22 revolver. So -
As a first time Glock owner I've found the Glock Store to be an awesome resource; for learning more about my Glock; for suggested upgrades and improvements - and the videos, for me - have been extremely helpful! <review>Wow. OK where do I start., and I'll be plain and honest, as I do few of these and frankly don't waste my time bashing businesses, I usually just don't give them my business. As a big online shopper of all things, but mostly firearms and accessories, I am always looking to try new companies, particularly companies that appear to move volume, as the generally offer the best deals. My rules (just a few things I feel as a customer) are really simple: have the product (if you don't let me know), have an accurate website (if it's BACKORDERED, or NOT YET AVAILABLE, just say so), and have good customer service (I mean, I work for a freakin' living, so put a little respect on it). On my first order with this company, for  G 43 accessories, they violated all three. <user_id>115931036887720991296<//user_id>< username>
Linda McWeeney< /username>
<time>1597766009331< /time><rating>5<//rating>< Text>
My husband was referred to this facility by our doctor for a hearing evaluation and new hearing aids.  If there were more than 5 stars we would certainly give it 10+ -- they are so beyond helpful and totally professional.

They gave us several options on hearing aids and the pros and cons of each.  He had his hearing test and everything was totally explained as to the extent of his hearing loss.

We bought the ones we wanted and went back the next week.  We figured he would just hand them to us and that would be it.  Not so, he spent a good deal of time adjusting them and letting my husband know just how to use them and adjust them.  We go back again in two weeks for a recheck  to see that all is working as it should.

Cannot give them enough praise!!  If you need hearing aids this is the one and only place to go.< /Text>

<UserId.>100829850564000645916< /UserId.><Name>Valente V</Name>< Text>
Not that good. The store itself is small, and currently with covid, they only allow one person inside at a time. There's not much room to form a line or wait for your order to be ready on the outside.

The mango green milk tea tasted more strongly of green tea than of mango, which is not necessary bad, but not what I was looking for. The selection of toppings is relatively small, and mostly flavors that may not be familiar if you're not from an Asian background.

It's nice that they give you the option of ice and sweetness levels, but I'd like to be able to ask for extra sweetness rather than only reduced sweetness. They do not have different sizes, but it's not tasty enough that I'd want a larger size anyways.

Prices are fairly standard for a boba place, but you have to pay an extra fifty cents per topping, even the first. They do not take Google/Apple/etc. Pay, and only take card for transactions over $6.00.

Overall, it may be good if you like flavors so subtle that you have to go on an adventure to find them, but if you like something tasty just go somewhere else.< /Text>

< Review>
A below average quality teashop. I had ordered the cocoa tea and asked for more sugar and they refused to give me. I mean I've never been to a tea shop that doesn't offer sugar!! Like Really? So I'd rather prefer other options where they get you what you need and not force you to drink what they have.</Review>

< UserId.>
103841624918385147503< /UserId.>
< Text>
I love the atmosphere of this restaurant. It is very quaint, and it feels like you are being served 1:1. I got the seco de pollo -- next time, I want to get their Peruvian breakfast with a maracuya juice. Their aji sauce is seriously legit too -- it seems like they crushed the fresh peppers themselves.

edit: I went again and tried their aguadito de pollo, pan con carne mixta, tamal de cerdo, and pescado frito. The soup, sandwich, and fried fish were out of this world! The fried fish especially was absolutely incredible. This is certainly a staple Peruvian restaurant in SF.</Text>

< Name>
Peter Wald</Name>
< time>
1508899868847</time>
<rating>5</rating>< text>
The Mission has a lot of very good Peruvian restaurants, but this one is my favorite by a good margin. The prices might seem a little high for such a hole-in-the-wall, but they are justified when you consider the quality of food and service. My only complaint is that they close so early (5pm on weekdays). Don't forget to bring cash.

On your first visit, go straight for the Pescado Frito ($16) and hit it with their green hot sauce if you like your food spicy. The fish is swai and it is battered and fried to order. It comes out hot and salty and flaky. I don't know of better fried fish in the city.<//text>

<Text>The best homestyle Peruvian restaurant in the city! I probably go here once a week because the food is so good. I love the Pescado frito and lomo saltado. The price is a bit steep for the neighborhood ($15-$17/plate) but the food is so worth it! You also need to order the alfajores. I've had alfajores from Argentina and they weren't this good. It has a great balance of sweetness and stickiness in the caramel and the short bread isn't hard - just right. < Review>
The second weekend in August, if you're not here, you should be. The Long Beach Jazz Festival is a habit that I have had for over 20 years. And don't intend to break it. The crowd is chill. The Lineup is always legendary. Even the vendors are great. This is, I believe, the only three day weekend jazz festival in Southern California. If it's a Rainbow Promotions event, it's a guaranteed good time.< /Review>
